    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Despite the Zip Code The Houses Are in Yonkers</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Edward Sheeran letter on Laura Stichter-Bryson's May 28 article holds Bronxville Village is part of Yonkers (S)6</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Laura Stichter-Bryson is not very credible when it comes to providing true facts on property outside the square mile radius of Bronxville Village in the 10708 zip code.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Laura Stichter-Bryson is not very credible when it comes to providing true facts on property outside the square mile radius of Bronxville Village in the 10708 zip code.</p>
        <p>When people think of Yonkers, they think of Sarah Lawrence College, Dunwoodie Seminary, Yonkers Raceway, Cross County Shopping Center, Central Park Avenue shopping district, Stew Leonard's, South Westchester Executive Park and the four-mile-long waterfront. They think of the convenience of two railroads and four parkways and, yes, they think of how the new Getty Square area will soon attract visitors and shoppers from all over, including Bronxville.</p>
        <p>EDWARD SHEERAN  Yonkers</p>
      </block>
